PETA spokesperson Pamela Anderson joined Maricopa County Sheriff Joe Arpaio on Wednesday to serve vegetarian meals to inmates at the jail . 
  Arpaio says cutting meat from the meals has saved an estimated $200,000 per year . 
  The jail has been serving vegetarian meals for 16 months and is the first in the country to go entirely vegetarian . 
  Anderson and PETA have come under fire for their association with the controversial sheriff . 
  Arpaio is notorious for his controversial opinions and racial profiling of Latinos . 
 